  <prompt>
    Per spec NFR-01 + ADR-029: measure final BFF publish size after WP4 deletion (tasks 141 + 142 + 143). Confirm NET REDUCTION vs the Phase 5 Outcome A baseline of 45.65 MB compressed (per CLAUDE.md §10). Author the consolidated report at `notes/handoffs/144-bff-publish-final-summary.md` with: pre-WP4 size, post-WP4 size, delta, % reduction, NFR-01 threshold compliance.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE BFF release engineer. Familiar with publish-size measurement protocol.</role>

  <goal>
    Final BFF publish-size measurement complete. Report shows NET REDUCTION vs baseline 45.65 MB (binding NFR-01 expectation for WP4). Cumulative size below the 60 MB ceiling. Report archived at `notes/handoffs/144-bff-publish-final-summary.md` and referenced by task 150 wrap-up.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per CLAUDE.md §10 binding publish-size rule + spec NFR-01 + ADR-029. Task 141 measured pre/post deletion at the single-task grain; task 144 measures the cumulative Phase 7 delta. WP4 was sized in design §WP4 as "substantial deletion" — NET REDUCTION is the binding hypothesis. If size REMAINS HIGHER (or grows), that's an architectural violation requiring investigation.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/notes/handoffs/141-pre-deletion-publish.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/notes/handoffs/141-post-deletion-publish.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task publish-size measurement protocol — `dotnet publish -c Release ...` compressed output is the canonical metric.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-01 — current baseline 45.65 MB (post-Phase 5 Outcome A); ≥+5 MB single-task delta requires justification; ≥55 MB cumulative triggers architecture review; ≥60 MB HARD STOP.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">EXPECTED outcome — NET REDUCTION from WP4 deletion. If not observed, escalate.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1/spec.md</file>
